{{Quote|Star-Lord T'Challa, leader of the [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]] and lost Prince of [[Wakanda]].|[[Watcher]]|What If... The Watcher Broke His Oath?}}
Prince '''T'Challa''' is the son of King [[T'Chaka/Ravager T'Challa|T'Chaka]] who was abducted by [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]] from his home country of [[Wakanda]] at a young age. He grew up with the Ravagers, where over time he taught them to change their way of life. Now stealing from the wicked and over-privileged of the galaxy to help the less-fortunate, becoming adored icons to the galaxy and he gained the name '''Star-Lord'''. He eventually traveled to [[Morag]], where he stole the [[Orb]] and hired [[Korath the Pursuer/Ravager T'Challa|Korath the Pursuer]]. He then met up with [[Nebula/Ravager T'Challa|Nebula]], who told him about the [[Embers of Genesis]], which could feed millions of planets. He then hatched, and executed the plan to steal the Embers from the [[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]]. Successful, he returned to [[Earth]] and his homeland, and reunited with his family.

Later, after rescuing [[Peter Quill/Ravager T'Challa|Peter Quill]] from [[Ego/Ravager T'Challa|Ego]], Star-Lord was chosen by [[Watcher]] as a member of the [[Guardians of the Multiverse]], paired with other heroes from other universes to stop an inter dimensional cosmic being known as [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]], who planned to destroy all traces of life in the [[Multiverse]]. After Star-Lord and his team were successful in [[Battle for the Multiverse|defeating]] Ultron, he soon returned to his universe. 

==Biography==
{{MD|T'Challa (Earth-21818)}}
===Early Life===
====Living in Wakanda====
[[File:W102 - 69875.png|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa speaks with his [[T'Chaka/Ravager T'Challa|father]]]]
{{Quote|I am tired of living in a bubble. There's an entire world out there, Baba."<br>"Yes, one of war, violence, hatred. That world has nothing to offer [[Wakanda]]."<br>"There must be more. But we must be brave enough to search for it.|T'Challa and [[T'Chaka/Ravager T'Challa|T'Chaka]]|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
T'Challa was born in [[Wakanda]] to [[T'Chaka/Ravager T'Challa|T'Chaka]] and [[Ramonda/Ravager T'Challa|Ramonda]], and had a younger sister, [[Shuri/Ravager T'Challa|Shuri]]. Due to Wakanda's isolation from the rest of the world, T'Challa became interested in what was outside of Wakanda's dome and although T'Chaka praised his son's explorer nature, he discouraged him from such idea. T'Chaka told T'Challa that the world outside of their country was nothing but violence and destruction. T'Challa did not believe his father, saying that the world must be much more than that, but Wakandans must be brave enough to search for it.{{Ref|WI102}}

====Kidnapped by Ravagers====
[[File:What If...? 27.png|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa is abducted by the [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]]]]
{{Quote|What you doing out there all by yourself anyway?"<br>"Exploring the world."<br>"Sounds fun. But why stop at one world, huh?|[[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu Udonta]] and T'Challa|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
In [[1988/Ravager T'Challa|1988]], T'Challa was practicing tossing the spear at night and accidentally tossed it outside [[Wakanda]]'s barrier. When T'Challa passed through the barrier to collect his spear, he watched to his amazement as a [[M-Ships|spaceship]] approached him. Two [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]], [[Kraglin Obfonteri/Ravager T'Challa|Kraglin Obfonteri]] and [[Taserface/Ravager T'Challa|Taserface]], brought T'Challa onboard their ship and took him into space to [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu Udonta]] who instantly realized that they got the [[Peter Quill/Ravager T'Challa|wrong kid]]. Obfonteri noted that they read significant cosmic signals in that area, and T'Challa commented that it was the Wakandan [[vibranium]] meteorite.
[[File:What If...? 30.png|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa talking to [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu Udonta]]]]
Udonta noticed that T'Challa was not intimidated by the Ravagers who abducted him and asked him what he was doing there all alone, to which T'Challa replied that he was exploring the world. Udonta told T'Challa that he should not stop at one world and promised to show him the entire galaxy, to T'Challa's great amazement. T'Challa agreed to stay with the Ravagers, and Udonta personally trained him to become one of them, treating T'Challa as his own son. Years later, T'Challa was told by Udonta that Wakanda had been destroyed in a war, although T'Challa was still longing to see [[Earth]] again.{{Ref|WI102}}

===Ravager===
====Legendary Star-Lord====
{{Quote|Star-Lord, if you had to pick a favorite..."<br>"Really, I could not say."<br>"I know, I know, so many heists, so many planets saved.|[[Korath the Pursuer/Ravager T'Challa|Korath the Pursuer]] and Star-Lord|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
Years later, T'Challa taught the [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]] to change their ways and become something more than just space pirates. Under T'Challa's 'Robin Hood' influence, the Ravagers become adored icons in the galaxy by stealing from the wicked and over-privileged of the galaxy to help the less-fortunate. T'Challa's deeds of saving people across the galaxy, earned him the title of the legendary outlaw and the name "Star-Lord."

Led by Star-Lord, the Ravagers enacted a robbery of the [[Central Bank]] on [[Tarnax IV]] which resulted in injury to some of the local [[Skrulls]]. The Ravagers also provided the weaponry to the [[Ankarans|Ankaran]] resistance group, although the mission was too dangerous even by their standards, and they barely made it out of [[Ankara]] alive. Star-Lord also saved a planet from the [[Kree]] army, led by [[Ronan the Accuser/Ravager T'Challa|Ronan the Accuser]], in their invasion which would be the species of [[Drax/Ravager T'Challa|Drax]].

Star-Lord encountered [[Thanos/Ravager T'Challa|Thanos]], a notorious figure in the galactic underworld, whose objective was to bring balance and prevent overpopulation by killing half of the universe's population. Star-Lord managed to persuade Thanos, convincing him that there were better ways to relocate the universe's resources, inspiring Thanos to abandon his genocidal plans and join the Ravagers. T'Challa also developed a romantic relationship with Thanos' adopted daughter [[Nebula/Ravager T'Challa|Nebula]], who also joined the Ravagers. T'Challa noticed that was a strained relationship between Nebula and Thanos and tried to get them to sort it out through therapy, although it was not effective.{{Ref|WI102}}

====Stealing the Orb====
[[File:Star-Lord T'Challa on Morag.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord successfully stealing the [[Orb]]]]
{{Quote|If we made like the old days, you'd only have half of your teeth. Besides, wouldn't you rather use it to jump-start the [[Krylorians]]' dying star?|Star-Lord to [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu Udonta]]|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
In [[2000s/Ravager T'Challa#2008|2008]], T'Challa discovered the [[Orb]] on [[Morag]] and arrived there with [[Yondu/Party Prince Thor|Yondu Udonta]] and other [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]] to steal it. Star-Lord managed to obtain the Orb from the [[Temple Vault]], using his [[Gravity Mine]], however, when he was about to leave, he was halted by [[Korath the Pursuer/Ravager T'Challa|Korath the Pursuer]] and the [[Sakaarans]] who were sent by [[Ronan the Accuser/Ravager T'Challa|Ronan]] to collect the Orb. However, when Star-Lord revealed his identity, Korath was shocked as he was a huge fan of Star-Lord and his work across the galaxy.
[[File:What If...? 4.png|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord reveals himself to [[Korath the Pursuer/Ravager T'Challa|Korath the Pursuer]]]]
Star-Lord found Korath's reaction off-putting but despite his admiration, Korath still intended to fight Star-Lord and retrieve the Orb. Star-Lord said that the artifact as powerful as the Orb should be in his possessions, to which Korath agreed but he could not disobey Ronan's orders. However, Korath offered Star-Lord to let him join the Ravagers, but Star-Lord replied that they were too staffed up for him to join. Korath understood Star-Lord's reasoning and prepared for a fight with him, still expressing his admiration towards Star-Lord.
[[File:15A4F8EA-B947-405B-A5BE-1470FBB87B1A.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord is cornered by the [[Sakaarans]]]]
Engaging in a duel, Star-Lord was able to evade most of Korath's attacks before he finally managed to hit Star-Lord once. Star-Lord praised Korath and they continued fighting, only for Korath to accidentally hit the Orb trap and getting electrocuted. The Sakaarans then opened fire at Star-Lord, so he took cover behind the column and then took them out with his Gravity Mine. Star-Lord then left the temple with unconscious Korath, however, he got surrounded by more Sakaarans who held him at the gunpoint. Star-Lord gave Ravagers a signal to cover him, so Udonta attacked the Sakaarans with his [[Yaka Arrow]], although not in time.
[[File:53F3181B-4611-44BE-BE79-BC88B2FB94D7.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord prepares to leave [[Morag]]]]
Udonta asked about Korath to which Star-Lord replied that he was the newest Ravager recruit. While making their way out of Morag, Udonta jokingly suggested selling the Orb to the highest bidder, just like the old times, to which Star-Lord replied that he would rather use it to jump-start the [[Krylorians]]' dying star, saving their system from extinction. Star-Lord and the Ravagers then left the planet on Star-Lord's ship ''[[Mandela]]'' and traveled to [[Contraxia]] to celebrate.{{Ref|WI102}}

===Theft of the Embers of Genesis===
====Secret Plan====
[[File:4C5087B1-8013-4CCA-8EE9-A4D1835E6445.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa takes a selfie with [[Drax/Ravager T'Challa|Drax]]]]
{{Quote|With one [[Embers of Genesis|ounce]], you can heal a dying planet in minutes. And with a payload the size we're talking..."<br>"We could feed billions of people on millions of worlds, and eradicate hunger across the galaxy.|[[Nebula/Ravager T'Challa|Nebula]] and T'Challa|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
T'Challa joined [[Korath the Pursuer/Ravager T'Challa|Korath the Pursuer]] and his fellow [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]] at the bar on [[Contraxia]], talking about their previous deeds, such as stopping [[Thanos/Ravager T'Challa|Thanos]] from his genocidal quest. T'Challa then went to a bar counter to pay for his drinks where he was greeted by [[Drax/Ravager T'Challa|Drax]] who was grateful to him for saving his planet from [[Ronan the Accuser/Ravager T'Challa|Ronan]]. Drax then took a photo of him with T'Challa for his [[Ovette/Ravager T'Challa|wife]] and [[Kamaria/Ravager T'Challa|daughter]].
[[File:What If...? 34.png|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa is approached by [[Nebula/Ravager T'Challa|Nebula]]]]
T'Challa was then approached by [[Nebula/Ravager T'Challa|Nebula]] who was rather displeased because of her father's presence, although T'Challa said that they should try to reconnect, since Thanos changed. Nebula said that it does not change the past and pointed at T'Challa's necklace which reminded him about Wakanda, asking if he ever wanted to return to his home. T'Challa then told Nebula that [[Wakanda]] was destroyed in the war, according to [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu Udonta]], making his [[T'Chaka/Ravager T'Challa|father]]'s words about the dangers of the world correct.
[[File:W102 - 0001478.png|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa speaks with [[Nebula/Ravager T'Challa|Nebula]]]]
Nebula told T'Challa and the Ravagers about the [[Embers of Genesis]], nutrient-rich cosmic dust with the power to terraform entire ecosystems. T'Challa commented that since one ounce was enough to heal a dying planet, an amount of the Embers they were discussing was able to feed billions of people on millions on worlds, eradicating hunger across the galaxy. Nebula informed the Ravagers that the Embers were in the possession of the [[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]] who became the notorious kingpin in the intergalactic underworld, filling the power vacuum, left by Thanos. However, Udonta rejected the plan, telling T'Challa that the Collector was too dangerous even for the Ravagers to handle, but T'Challa was able to convince him to participate anyway.
[[File:Knowhere on screen.png|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa describes [[Knowhere]] to the [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|team]]]]
T'Challa and Nebula devised a plan to infiltrate the [[Collector's Museum]] by pretending to be the sellers of the [[Orb]], while others would be made the diversion for the [[Black Order/Ravager T'Challa|Black Order]] outside. With Tivan being distracted by Nebula and Udonta, T'Challa would search the museum for the Embers. However, T'Challa also discussed with Nebula a secret part of the plan, in which Nebula would pretend to betray the Ravagers to repay the debt to Tivan.{{Ref|WI102}}

====Infiltrating the Museum====
[[File:38DDE6D5-8354-478E-A6C8-8E95E69B4532.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord scours the [[Collector's Museum]]]]
{{Quote|Dude, we have to go!"<br>"Where are you going? Come back.|Star-Lord and [[Howard the Duck/Ravager T'Challa|Howard the Duck]]|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
The [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]] arrived on the [[Knowhere]] and proceeded with their operation, with Star-Lord hiding inside the containment box with [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu Udonta]] and [[Nebula/Ravager T'Challa|Nebula]]. [[Proxima Midnight/Ravager T'Challa|Proxima Midnight]] attempted to run a security scan on the box, only to be summoned outside to deal with [[Thanos/Ravager T'Challa|Thanos]] and [[Korath the Pursuer/Ravager T'Challa|Korath the Pursuer]] causing a disturbance outside of the museum. While Nebula and Udonta went to speak with the [[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]], Star-Lord left the box and went to search for the [[Embers of Genesis]].
[[File:What If...? 45.png|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord meets [[Howard the Duck/Ravager T'Challa|Howard the Duck]]]]
Looking through Tivan's collection, Star-Lord encountered [[Howard the Duck/Ravager T'Challa|Howard the Duck]] who was one of Tivan's exhibits. Star-Lord tried to ask Howard about the Embers but when Howard's explanation went to elaborate, Star-Lord just opened a containment unit and asked him to show the direction himself. On the way to the flora section, Howard stayed at the bar for a drink, however, Star-Lord had to run, since the [[Black Order/Ravager T'Challa|Black Order]] initiated an alarm.
[[File:Commodore, Necrocraft, Mining Pod, Star Blaster What If... 1.02.png|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord finds a [[Royal Talon Fighter]]]]
Star-Lord ran to the spaceship sector where he found his [[vibranium]] necklace resonating with a [[Royal Talon Fighter]] that Tivan had in his possession. Star-Lord went onboard of the Fighter where he discovered the mannequins in [[Dora Milaje/Ravager T'Challa|Dora Milaje]] uniforms and a recorded message from [[T'Chaka/Ravager T'Challa|T'Chaka]] who was looking for his son for years. Star-Lord realized that [[Wakanda]] was still alive and well and Udonta was lying to him the whole time, before Nebula went on with her part of the plan and pretending to sell Star-Lord off to the Collector.{{Ref|WI102}}

====Battle with the Collector====
[[File:Corvus imprisons Yondu and T'Challa2.png|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord is imprisoned by [[Corvus Glaive/Ravager T'Challa|Corvus Glaive]]]]
{{Quote|A pity. You abandoned your [[Wakanda|home]] and [[Golden Tribe/Ravager T'Challa|family]], and now, your [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|new family]] has abandoned you. Karma."<br>"Maybe you haven't heard. A [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravager]] never flies solo.|[[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]] and Star-Lord|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
Star-Lord was imprisoned at a cell with other [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]] caught by the [[Black Order/Ravager T'Challa|Black Order]], however, he was much more concerned about [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu Udonta]]'s lie. He confronted Udonta about him lying about [[Wakanda]]'s demise, to which Udonta replied that he wanted Star-Lord to get free from the shackles from his past, so he could embrace his true self of the explorer. Udonta wanted Star-Lord to leave the [[Earth]] in the past and be with the Ravagers, his true family but Star-Lord said that they are not his family and never were.
[[File:W102 - 784798.png|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord decries the [[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]]'s practices]]
They were interrupted by [[Corvus Glaive/Ravager T'Challa|Corvus Glaive]] who brought Star-Lord to the [[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]]. Knocked out by Glaive, Star-Lord found himself inside the containment unit. The Collector started taunting Star-Lord about making him a new exhibit for his museum, to which Star-Lord told him that he was a mere [[human]]. Annoyed at Star-Lord, the Collector ordered [[Ebony Maw/Ravager T'Challa|Ebony Maw]] to dissect him and strip his remains for parts, leaving him with Star-Lord and [[Carina/Ravager T'Challa|Carina]].
[[File:Collector and weapons.png|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord fights the [[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]]]]
Star-Lord used his opportunity to free himself by breaking the glass with his necklace and attempted to strike Maw, only for Maw to stop Star-Lord with his telekinesis. However, Carina turned against her master and shot Maw, letting Star-Lord escape. Star-Lord thanked Carina and ran towards the exit from the museum, only to be confronted by the Collector himself who attacked him using the [[Kronan]] gauntlet. Star-Lord tried to fight the Collector but found him too strong for the close combat, especially with the artifacts in his possessions, such as the [[Dark Matter Dagger]] and the [[Necroswords]].
[[File:79D9ACA1-B87D-41C1-A4EC-B9205BA5169E.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord defeats the [[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]]]]
Star-Lord could barely avoid the swords until one of them pinned him against the containment unit, rendering him defenseless. The Collector mocked Star-Lord for abandoning his family, only to be abandoned by his new family, however, he was proven wrong when Udonta rescued Star-Lord. Star-Lord and Udonta confronted the Collector in a battle but since he was too strong for them, Star-Lord decided to trick him. Distracting the Collector in a battle, Udonta managed to steal his bracelet that he used to control his museum, before Star-Lord pushed him inside the containment unit. Although the Collector threatened to find Star-Lord and get his revenge, he was left on Carina's mercy who unleashed all of the Collector's prisoners on him.
[[File:F9FB0DD3-62C6-4FD6-A9D2-86510645F92B.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa is encouraged to return to [[Wakanda]]]]
T'Challa and Udonta then stole the [[Royal Talon Fighter]] from Tivan's collection and left the [[Knowhere]], leaving Tivan behind. T'Challa was contacted by Nebula who told him that all crew is alive and well, so T'Challa told them to meet at a rendezvous point, before noticing that [[Cosmo the Spacedog/Ravager T'Challa|Cosmo]] ran away from Tivan's collection and snuck aboard their ship. T'Challa then took Cosmo in as his pet. Udonta tried to apologize to T'Challa for lying to him about Wakanda's fate but T'Challa forgave him, saying that Udonta did show him the universe, just as he promised. However, T'Challa also said that since he knew the truth, he was not sure where he belongs to, and Udonta told him that he should follow his heart which will bring him to the place he belongs to.{{Ref|WI102}}

===Returning to Wakanda===
[[File:Episode-poster-2 (1).png|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa returns to [[Wakanda]]]]
{{Quote|My son. I knew you would find your way home to us."<br>"I'm sorry it took me so long. Let me introduce you to the [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|family]] I made along the way.|[[T'Chaka/Ravager T'Challa|T'Chaka]] and T'Challa|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
T'Challa, [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu Udonta]], and [[Cosmo the Spacedog/Ravager T'Challa|Cosmo]] met up with the other [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravagers]] and T'Challa told them he wanted to return to [[Wakanda]]. Together, they took the ''[[Mandela]]'' to [[Earth]] and landed outside of [[Birnin Zana]]. T'Challa led the Ravagers into the [[Citadel]] and finally reunited with his family. He then apologized to [[T'Chaka/Ravager T'Challa|T'Chaka]] for being absent for so long and introduced his family to the Ravagers.
[[File:W102 - 369874.png|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa reunites with his family]]
Following T'Challa's return, the Wakandans held a celebration for him, and during it, T'Chaka asked how he ended up on the Ravager ship in the first place. Flustered, Udonta was trying to explain that they kidnapped him by accident, but T'Challa instead told his father that he got lost and the Ravagers found him and gave him a home.{{Ref|WI102}}

===[[Guardians of the Multiverse]]===
====Recruited by the Watcher====
{{Quote|Stay here. Leave this fight to us."<br>"I got it. Yeah. Hang back with the [[Watcher|giant baby-man cape dude]].|Star-Lord and [[Peter Quill/Ravager T'Challa|Peter Quill]]|What If... The Watcher Broke His Oath?}}
After hearing that [[Ego/Ravager T'Challa|Ego]] had arrived, T'Challa and the Ravagers left [[Wakanda]] and travelled to [[St. Charles]], [[Missouri]] in order to stop him from proceeding with his [[Ego's Expansion|expansion]]. Star-Lord located Ego in a Dairy Queen and broke inside, rescuing [[Peter Quill/Ravager T'Challa|Peter Quill]], and placing a bomb on Ego. As Ego and the Dairy Queen exploded, Star-Lord flew Quill to safety and placed him in a grassy area. As Star-Lord was telling Quill to stay where he was, Quill informed him of someone behind him.
[[File:The Watcher selects chosen Ones (Star-Lord)2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord witnesses [[Watcher]] selecting him]]
Star-Lord saw [[Watcher]] who told him he had been chosen and transported him to a pub in a dimension outside of space and time. T'Challa then met [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]], [[Strange Supreme]], [[Thor/Party Prince Thor|Thor]], [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]], and [[Gamora/Sakaarian Iron Man|Gamora]]. They were then all startled when the Watcher appeared before them, with T'Challa expressing discontent with the Watcher's abrupt surprises. The Watcher informed them of [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]] and Strange explained the [[Infinity Stones]] to them. After eating Chinese food, the Watcher dubbed them as the [[Guardians of the Multiverse]], before telling them they were ready and transported via [[Wormhole|portal]] to an uninhabited planet on a different universe.{{Ref|WI109}}

====Fighting Ultron====
[[File:Star-Lord -Protection Spell1.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Star-Lord admiring the protection spell]]
{{Quote|Did you get [[Soul Stone|it]]?"<br>"As [[Yondu/Ravager T'Challa|Yondu]] says, 'Never doubt sticky fingers.'|[[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]] and Star-Lord|What If... The Watcher Broke His Oath?}}
Once on the planet, [[Strange Supreme]] materialized drinks for the [[Guardians of the Multiverse]] and proposed a toast. As the toast grew awkward, T'Challa stepped forwards and gave the toast himself. Thor then accidentally alerted [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Infinity Ultron]] to their location. Strange then threw protection spells on all of them, in which Star-Lord was fascinated upon receiving his.
[[File:T'Challa Soul Stone.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa steals the [[Soul Stone]]]]
Star-Lord then gave [[Captain Carter/Super Soldier Peggy Carter|Captain Carter]] a lift up into the sky and jumped onto Ultron's back, stealing the [[Soul Stone]] from his armor. Ultron then blasted Star-Lord away, causing Star-Lord to fall roughly onto the ground. To the other's relief, he had the Stone in his possession, and handed it over to Carter. After Ultron realized what had happened, Strange opened up a [[Inter-Dimensional Portal|portal]] for them to escape and Star-Lord left through it.{{Ref|WI109}}
[[File:What-if-the-watcher-broke-his-oath-review-gamora-tchalla-starlord-and-party-thor.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa and the rest of the Guardians confront [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Infinity Ultron]]]]
The team arrived at Ultron's universe where [[Gamora/Sakaarian Iron Man|Gamora]] and [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]] were waiting for them, they were then confronted by [[Black Widow/Age of Ultron|Black Widow]], the only survivor of this universe, Star-Lord quickly took a fighting stance until Captain Carter told them to stand down and earned Black Widow's trust. When Ultron came and tried to get to Soul Stone away from Black Widow, who was in possession of the Soul Stone. Star-Lord and the Guardians attacked him. When the Guardians survived his attacks, an exasperated Ultron remarked that he could destroy galaxies with a thought and angrily asked why they would not die before unleashing the Stones' full power in an attempt to obliterate the Guardians and the greater galaxy they were in completely.

However, Strange simultaneously reversed his actions before absorbing the blast by eating it. Dumbstruck by what Strange had just done, Ultron was then tackled into a building and blasted at by Star-Lord, though Ultron recovered and threw Star-Lord away from him and onto [[Thor/Party Prince Thor|Thor]] and [[Gamora/Sakaarian Iron Man|Gamora]]. Upon recovering, Star-Lord participated in attacking Ultron along with the rest of the Guardians. However, Ultron used the [[Time Stone]] to slow down time and recover the Soul Stone but the bubble was broken by Strange Supreme, who had his own Time Stone. After Strange used his monstrous form to subdue Ultron, Star-Lord was on guard as Gamora used the Soul Stone to activate the [[Infinity Crusher]] to destroy Ultron. However, due to the stones being from another universe, the Crusher had no effect on the stones. As Ultron appeared and attacked Strange with an energy blast from all six stones in order to dissolve his protection spells, which left the Guardians defenseless, T'Challa was thrown to a nearby building due to the blast. Fortunately, due to [[Black Widow/Age of Ultron|Black Widow]] launching an arrow containing [[Arnim Zola/Age of Ultron|Arnim Zola]] into Ultron eyes, therefore killing him on the inside, the [[Battle for the Multiverse|battle]] was over.

====Killmonger's Betrayal====
{{Quote|Hand over the [[Infinity Stones|stones]], cousin."<br>"I'm not your cousin.|Star-Lord and [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]]|What If... The Watcher Broke His Oath?}}
However, tensions resurfaced when [[Erik Killmonger/Killmonger's War|Erik Killmonger]] used Ultron's [[Infinity Armor]] to acquire the [[Infinity Stones]]. Surprised by this, T'Challa asked his cousin what he was doing to which Killmonger replied that they could use the stones to fix their problems back in their universes. Attempting to reason with him, T'Challa calmly told Killmonger to hand over the Stones but he refused. As T'Challa and the rest of the Guardians prepared to face him, Killmonger used the Stones to repel the guardians, possibly killing them had he gone on for too long. Zola, who now had complete control over Ultron's former body, also tried take the stones for himself. This resulted in both of them getting into a deadlock for the stones while Strange encased them into a pocket dimension. With the Multiverse secured, T'Challa and the rest of the Guardians retuned to the pub pocket dimension to celebrate their success.{{Ref|WI109}}

====Returning to His Universe====
[[File:T'Challa and Quill (What If).png|{{AltFloat}}|T'Challa teaches [[Peter Quill/Ravager T'Challa|Quill]] how to shoot a [[Quad Blasters|Quad Blaster]]]]
Following the [[Battle for the Multiverse]], [[Watcher]] congratulated T'Challa and the other [[Guardians of the Multiverse]] for saving the [[Multiverse]] from [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Infinity Ultron]] and stated that the pub's door would bring them back to their home universes at the exact moment they left. Upon returning to his native universe, he recruited [[Peter Quill/Ravager T'Challa|Peter Quill]] and began to teach him how to use a blaster by fighting with him.{{Ref|WI109}}

===Continued Multiverse Adventures===
T'Challa returned to reassemble with the other [[Guardians of the Multiverse]] and took a group photo, which included new members of the team. However, he eventually left the team.{{Ref|WI307}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Former Powers===
*'''Protection Spell''': [[File:Star-Lord -Protection Spell2.jpg|thumb|250px|Star-Lord receiving a protection spell]] During the Battle for the Multiverse, [[Strange Supreme]] summoned a [[Guardian Vishanti]] protection spell and placed it on his [[Guardians of the Multiverse|teammates]]. However, this spell wore off after several hits from [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]].
**'''Physical Augmentation''': The protection spell augmented his condition, as he was capable of grabbing Ultron and slamming him into the ground.
**'''Weapon Enhancement''': The protection spell augmented T'Challa's weapons, allowing his quad blasters to injure Infinity Ultron during the battle.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|I might be able to help with that. I've stolen more from worse.|T'Challa|What If... The Watcher Broke His Oath?}}
*'''Master Thief''': T'Challa is a legendary outlaw with two decades of experience as a [[Ravagers/Ravager T'Challa|Ravager]], having been involved in many heists and saving many planets, such as the [[Central Bank]] heist of [[Tarnax IV]], when he armed the Ankaran resistance, or when he saved the planet from a [[Kree]] invasion (which took six days). He easily infiltrated the [[Temple Vault]], stole the [[Orb]] and escaped [[Morag]]. He was also able to steal Ultron's [[Soul Stone]] when fighting with [[Infinity Ultron/Age of Ultron|Ultron]].
{{Quote|You do not disappoint, my lord. So nimble, so spry.|[[Korath the Pursuer/Ravager T'Challa|Korath the Pursuer]] to Star-Lord|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
*'''Master Martial Artist''': [[File:T'Challa Star-Lord vs Collector What If...? Still.png|thumb|250px|Star-Lord fighting against the [[Collector/Ravager T'Challa|Collector]]]] T'Challa was trained by Yondu and the Ravagers in combat, as he was able to fight against Korath, the Collector, and Infinity Ultron.
*'''Expert Marksman''': ''To be added''
*'''Master Acrobat''': T'Challa is greatly agile, which he uses during his fights, such as dodging Korath's hits.
*'''Genius-Level Intellect''': T'Challa is a highly intelligent galactic outlaw with two decades of experience. He is a skilled debater, as he convinced Thanos, a tactical genius in his own right, to not decimate half of the universe.
{{Quote|Amazing. I have no notes. A perfect plan.|[[Korath the Pursuer/Ravager T'Challa|Korath the Pursuer]] to Star-Lord|What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?}}
*'''Master Tactician''': He is a capable strategist, planning a heist to obtain the Embers of Genesis, and form another plan to have Nebula fake her treachery.
*'''Bilingualism''': T'Challa is fluent in his native Xhosa, as well as English, albeit with a Wakandan accent.

