==Behind the Scenes==
*Due to enjoying the experience of voicing Star-Lord in ''[[What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?]]'', [[Chadwick Boseman]] had discussed with [[Kevin Feige]] and [[Ryan Coogler]] to incorporate some elements of this "{{WPS|Gung ho}}" version of T'Challa for [[T'Challa|Black Panther]] in ''[[Black Panther: Wakanda Forever]]''.<ref>[https://tvline.com/2021/08/18/chadwick-boseman-what-if-performance-influence-black-panther-sequel/ ''What If...?'': Chadwick Boseman's Lighter, 'Gung Ho' Take on T'Challa Was to Carry Over Into ''Black Panther 2'']</ref>
*The crew behind ''[[What If...?]]'' planned to make a spin-off show starring this version of T'Challa. However, plans for this spin-off were left in limbo following [[Chadwick Boseman]]'s death. According to director [[Bryan Andrews]], Boseman was possibly unaware of these plans, but believed he would have loved the concept.<ref>[https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/marvel-what-if-season-1-finale-tchalla-spin-off-chadwick-boseman-1235082366/ Inside Marvel’s ‘What If…?’ Finale, Season 2 Plans and the T’Challa Spinoff That Never Was]</ref>

